CDP Page.getResourceTree returns a FrameResourceTree: { frame: { id, url, securityOrigin, ... }, childFrames: [...], resources: [{ url, type, mimeType, contentLength, ... }] }. The resource types from CDP are: Document, Stylesheet, Image, Media, Font, Script, TextTrack, XHR, Fetch, Prefetch, EventSource, WebSocket, Manifest, SignedExchange, Ping, CSPViolationReport, Preflight, Other. Flatten the tree recursively to collect all resources across all frames. The contentLength may not always be available — set to -1 or undefined when absent.

Debugger management pattern:
```typescript
const alreadyAttached = isCapturing(tabId);
if (!alreadyAttached) {
  try {
    await chrome.debugger.attach({ tabId }, '1.3');
  } catch (err) {
    // Provide helpful error
    throw new Error(`Failed to attach debugger...`);
  }
}
try {
  await chrome.debugger.sendCommand({ tabId }, 'Page.enable');
  const tree = await chrome.debugger.sendCommand({ tabId }, 'Page.getResourceTree');
  // ... process tree
} finally {
  if (!alreadyAttached) {
    await chrome.debugger.detach({ tabId }).catch(() => {});
  }
}
```

